    "what_description": "Microlepia smithii is a species of fern in the family Dennstaedtiaceae, native to New Zealand. It is a diploid plant with a chromosome number of 2n= 144. Microlepia smithii has fronds that are 30-120 cm in length, pinnatifid to pinnate, and have a deltoid to ovate base. The pinnae are 3-10 cm in length, alternate to subopposite, and have a cuneate to attenuate base. The rhizome is creeping to ascending, with scales 0.5-2 cm in length.",
